.TH "vmw_kms_sou_readback" 9 "vmw_kms_sou_readback" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
vmw_kms_sou_readback \- Perform a readback from the screen object system to a buffer-object backed framebuffer.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" vmw_kms_sou_readback
.BI "(struct vmw_private *dev_priv "  ","
.BI "struct drm_file *file_priv "  ","
.BI "struct vmw_framebuffer *vfb "  ","
.BI "struct drm_vmw_fence_rep __user *user_fence_rep "  ","
.BI "struct drm_vmw_rect *vclips "  ","
.BI "uint32_t num_clips "  ","
.BI "struct drm_crtc *crtc "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "dev_priv" 12
Pointer to the device private structure.
.IP "file_priv" 12
Pointer to a struct drm_file identifying the caller.
Must be set to NULL if \fIuser_fence_rep\fP is NULL.
.IP "vfb" 12
Pointer to the buffer-object backed framebuffer.
.IP "user_fence_rep" 12
User-space provided structure for fence information.
Must be set to non-NULL if \fIfile_priv\fP is non-NULL.
.IP "vclips" 12
Array of clip rects.
.IP "num_clips" 12
Number of clip rects in \fIvclips\fP.
.IP "crtc" 12
If crtc is passed, readback on that crtc only.
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Returns 0 on success, negative error code on failure. -ERESTARTSYS if
interrupted.
